arctgz(7)						   Miscellaneous Information Manual						    arctgz(7)

NAME
       arctgz  -  safety-first	project	 initialisation, configuration management, archival compilation and extraction library for the arctgz archive
       format

SYNOPSIS
       use arctgz::{
	   init, load_config, save_config, compile, extract,
	   ArctgzConfig, ArctgzManifest, FileEntry, ArctgzError
       };
       use std::path::Path;

       fn init(project_path: &Path, force: bool) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn load_config(project_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzConfig, ArctgzError>;
       fn save_config(project_path: &Path, config: &ArctgzConfig) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn compile(
	   project_path: &Path,
	   output_dir: Option<&Path>,
	   force: bool
       ) -> Result<PathBuf, ArctgzError>;
       fn extract(
	   archive_path: &Path,
	   output_dir: &Path,
	   force: bool
       ) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;

       struct ArctgzConfig {
	   pub name:	String,
	   pub version: String,
	   pub include: Vec<String>,
       }

       struct ArctgzManifest {
	   pub name:	String,
	   pub version: String,
	   pub created: DateTime<Utc>,
	   pub files:	BTreeMap<String, FileEntry>,
       }

       struct FileEntry {
	   pub size:   u64,
	   pub sha512: String,
       }

       enum ArctgzError { ... }

DESCRIPTION
       The arctgz library provides a safe, cross-platform API for the full lifecycle of an arctgz project:  scaffolding,  configuration,  compilation
       into a compressed archive, and verified extraction.

       All  operations	enforce	 strict path confinement, validate metadata before touching the filesystem, and use atomic file operations to prevent
       corruption and TOCTOU (time-of-check to time-of-use) races.

       The core functionality includes:

       • init() – scaffold a new project directory with a default configuration and an empty resource folder.

       • load_config() – read and validate an existing project configuration.

       • save_config() – atomically write a validated configuration back to disk.

       • compile() – bundle the project files and configuration into a signed (SHA-512) compressed archive.

       • extract() – unpack an archive, verifying every file's integrity against the embedded manifest and preventing path traversal attacks.

       All paths are resolved with std::fs::canonicalize() (equivalent to realpath(3)), so symbolic links are followed during the home-directory con‐
       finement check.	The library is fully tested on Linux, macOS, and Windows.

INSTALLATION
       This man page can be installed system-wide using the provided installer script:

       curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash

       The script places arctgz.7 into /usr/local/share/man/man7/ and updates the man database.	 To uninstall, run:

       curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash -s -- uninstall

FUNCTIONS
       init(project_path, force)
	      Initialises a new arctgz project at project_path.

	      Arguments:

		     project_path
			    A reference to a std::path::Path.  The path must not be empty and must reside (after canonicalisation) under the  current
			    user's home directory.  If the path does not exist, it will be created; otherwise it must be a directory.

		     force  If	true,  skip the non-empty directory check.  However, an existing arctgz.init file will still cause an AlreadyInitial‐
			    ized error.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(()) on success, or an ArctgzError describing the failure.

	      Side effects (only after all safety checks pass):

		     • Creates the project directory (and parents, if needed).

		     • Creates the include/ subdirectory.

		     • Writes a default arctgz.init configuration file atomically (using create_new(true)).

	      Security checks (performed before any filesystem modification):

		     • Home directory confinement – the canonicalised project path must start with the canonicalised home directory.  Symlink attacks
		       are neutralised.

		     • Path validity – rejects empty paths, and rejects existing files (as opposed to directories).

		     • Directory emptiness (unless force is true).

       load_config(project_path)
	      Reads and validates the arctgz.init file from the given project directory.

	      Arguments:

		     project_path
			    Path to the project root (must contain an arctgz.init file).

	      Return value:
		     Ok(ArctgzConfig) if the file exists, contains valid JSON, and passes validate().  On failure,  returns  an	 ArctgzError  variant
		     (ConfigNotFound, ConfigLoadError, or ConfigValidation).

       save_config(project_path, config)
	      Writes  a validated ArctgzConfig back to the project's arctgz.init file atomically.  The operation first writes the JSON to a temporary
	      file (arctgz.tmp) and then renames it over the original.	This prevents corruption if the process crashes mid-write.

	      Arguments:

		     project_path
			    Path to the project root.

		     config An ArctgzConfig instance to save.  Must pass validate() before saving.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(()) on success, or an ArctgzError (ConfigValidation, ConfigSaveError, or Json).

       compile(project_path, output_dir, force)
	      Compiles the project into a compressed, integrity-verified arctgz archive (.artgz).

	      The function:

	      • Loads the project configuration via load_config().

	      • Collects the arctgz.init file and all files listed in the include array, recursively  adding  directories  while  rejecting  symbolic
		links.

	      • Computes a SHA-512 hash for every file and records size + hash in an ArctgzManifest.

	      • Creates a gzip-compressed tar archive containing the files and the manifest.json entry.

	      • Writes the archive atomically via a temporary file and rename.

	      Arguments:

		     project_path
			    Path to the project root.

		     output_dir
			    Optional output directory.	If None, the archive is placed in project_path/dist/.

		     force  If true, overwrite an existing archive; otherwise fail if the archive already exists.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(PathBuf)  containing  the  full	 path to the created archive, or an ArctgzError (including IncludeFileNotFound, SymlinkNotAl‐
		     lowed, or Io for an already-existing archive when force is false).

	      Safety:

		     • Symlinks are rejected to prevent reference leaks outside the project.

		     • The entire archive is written atomically; a crash mid-write leaves no partial archive.

       extract(archive_path, output_dir, force)
	      Extracts a previously compiled arctgz archive, verifying the integrity of every file and guarding against path traversal attacks.

	      The function:

	      • Opens and decompresses the archive.

	      • Locates the embedded manifest.json and deserialises it.

	      • Checks that every file path in the archive is relative and does not contain .. (parent directory) components; rejects absolute paths.

	      • Verifies that all files listed in the manifest are present in the archive and vice versa.

	      • Recomputes the SHA-512 hash of each file and compares it to the manifest entry; a mismatch aborts with ChecksumMismatch.

	      • Writes files to output_dir, creating subdirectories as needed, and refusing to overwrite existing files unless force is true.

	      Arguments:

		     archive_path
			    Path to the .artgz archive.

		     output_dir
			    Destination directory; will be created if it does not exist.

		     force  If true, overwrite existing files; otherwise abort on conflict.

	      Return value:
		     Ok(()) on success, or an ArctgzError (ManifestNotFound, ChecksumMismatch, ExtractError for unsafe paths, or  Io  for  file	 con‐
		     flicts).

TYPES
       ArctgzConfig
	      Represents the project configuration stored in arctgz.init.

       Fields:

	      name   Project name (default "untitled").	 Valid characters: alphanumeric, -, and _.  Maximum length 255 characters.

	      version
		     Semantic version string (default "0.1.0"), validated against the semver crate.

	      include
		     List  of  relative	 resource paths (default []).  Each path must be relative, must not contain .. (parent directory) components,
		     and the list may contain at most 100 entries.

       validate()
       Validates all fields according to the rules above.  Returns Ok(()) or an ArctgzError::ConfigValidation with a human-readable message.

       The struct is serialised/deserialised with #[serde(deny_unknown_fields)], so unknown JSON keys in the configuration file will cause a  deseri‐
       alisation error.

       ArctgzManifest
	      Embedded inside every compiled archive as manifest.json.

	      Fields:

		     name   Project name (copied from config).

		     version
			    Project version (copied from config).

		     created
			    UTC timestamp of archive creation (chrono::DateTime<Utc>).

		     files  A BTreeMap mapping archived paths (relative strings) to FileEntry records.

       FileEntry
	      Metadata for a single file in the archive.

	      Fields:

		     size   File size in bytes.

		     sha512 Hexadecimal string of the file's SHA-512 hash.

       ArctgzError
	      An enumeration covering all failure cases.  Each variant holds a descriptive message (or source error) to aid debugging.

       Variants:

	      Io(std::io::Error)
		     Filesystem I/O error (e.g., creating directories, writing files, archive already exists).

	      Json(serde_json::Error)
		     JSON serialisation or deserialisation failure.

	      AlreadyInitialized
		     An arctgz.init file already exists in the target directory during init().

	      InvalidPath(String)
		     The supplied path is empty or is an existing file, not a directory.

	      PathNotAllowed(String)
		     The canonicalised project path lies outside the user's home directory.

	      DirectoryNotEmpty(String)
		     The target directory exists, is not empty, and force was false.

	      ConfigValidation(String)
		     A configuration validation rule failed (e.g., invalid name, version, or include).

	      ConfigNotFound(String)
		     load_config() could not find the arctgz.init file.

	      ConfigLoadError(String)
		     load_config() encountered an I/O error or invalid JSON.

	      ConfigSaveError(String)
		     save_config() failed during the write or rename step.

	      SymlinkNotAllowed(String)
		     A symbolic link was encountered during archive compilation; symlinks are forbidden.

	      IncludeFileNotFound(String)
		     A file listed in the include array does not exist on disk during compilation.

	      ManifestNotFound
		     The archive being extracted does not contain a manifest.json entry.

	      ChecksumMismatch(String, String, String)
		     A	file's	actual SHA-512 hash does not match the one recorded in the manifest.  The three fields are: file path, expected hash,
		     actual hash.

	      ExtractError(String)
		     Generic extraction failure (unsafe path, missing file, etc.).

EXAMPLE
   Basic initialisation
       use std::path::Path;
       use arctgz;

       fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
	   let project_path = Path::new("./my-project");
	   arctgz::init(project_path, false)?;
	   println!("Project created.");
	   Ok(())
       }

       After running the above, the directory looks like:
       my-project/
       |-- arctgz.init
       `-- include/

   Editing configuration
       use arctgz::{load_config, save_config};

       fn configure(project: &std::path::Path) -> Result<(), arctgz::ArctgzError> {
	   let mut config = load_config(project)?;
	   config.name = "hello-world".into();
	   config.include.push("assets".into());
	   save_config(project, &config)?;
	   Ok(())
       }

   Compiling and extracting
       use arctgz::{compile, extract};

       fn roundtrip(project: &std::path::Path) -> Result<(), arctgz::ArctgzError> {
	   let archive = compile(project, None, false)?;
	   let out_dir = project.parent().unwrap().join("output");
	   extract(&archive, &out_dir, false)?;
	   Ok(())
       }

FILES
       arctgz.init
	      JSON configuration file.	Written atomically by init() and save_config().	 The library never truncates an existing file unless  explic‐
	      itly overwritten via save_config().

       include/
	      An empty directory created during initialisation.	 It is intended to hold resource files for later compilation/archiving.

       dist/<name>-<version>.artgz
	      Default output location for compiled archives (when output_dir is None).

       manifest.json
	      Embedded inside every .artgz archive; contains the project metadata and integrity records.

ENVIRONMENT
       HOME (Unix) / USERPROFILE (Windows)
	      The library obtains the current user's home directory through the dirs crate.  If the variable is not set, a platform-specific fallback
	      is  attempted.   If no home directory can be determined, init() will fail with PathNotAllowed for any path (even relative ones) because
	      confinement cannot be verified.

SECURITY
       • Path confinement: only paths inside the canonicalised home directory are allowed for initialisation.  Symlink traversal is  fully  mitigated
	 by canonicalising both the project path and the home directory.

       • No  side effects before validation: init() resolves the path and performs all security checks before creating any directories.	 Thus, even a
	 failed call with a path outside the home directory will not leave unwanted directories on disk.

       • Atomic configuration writes: the use of create_new(true) for init() prevents TOCTOU attacks when creating the initial config.	save_config()
	 and compile() write to a temporary file and rename, ensuring the target file is never left in an incomplete state.

       • Archive integrity: every file in the archive is hashed with SHA-512.  The manifest is embedded and verified during extraction; any  mismatch
	 aborts with ChecksumMismatch.

       • Path traversal prevention: extract() rejects any archived path that is absolute or contains .. components, preventing zip-slip attacks.

       • Symlink rejection: compile() refuses to include symbolic links, ensuring archives contain only regular files and directories.

       • Input	validation: configuration fields are strictly validated.  Unknown JSON keys are rejected, preventing accidental or malicious settings
	 from entering the project metadata.

NOTES
       The library is intended to be used as a building block for higher-level tools.  It does not impose any locking mechanism; concurrent calls  on
       the  same  directory  may  race (see TOCTOU considerations in the security section).  Users should serialise access when operating on the same
       project from multiple processes or threads.

VERSION
       arctgz 0.4.0 – full project lifecycle: initialisation, configuration management, archive compilation with SHA-512 integrity, and verified  ex‐
       traction.  Future releases may add cryptographic signing and post-extraction recipes.

SEE ALSO
       semver(7), realpath(3), serde_json(5), dirs(7), flate2(7), tar(5), sha2(7)

BUGS
       • The include/ directory is always created empty; files must be added manually before compilation.

       • Concurrent  init calls on the same path are not serialised and may lead to one process failing with AlreadyInitialized while another has al‐
	 ready created the directory.

       • The library does not clean up the include/ directory if the configuration write fails halfway through initialisation.

       • Archive format does not yet include cryptographic signatures; integrity is based solely on SHA-512 hashes.

